org.sat4j.minisat.core
インタフェース PrimeImplicantStrategy

既知の実装クラスの一覧:
CounterBasedPrimeImplicantStrategy, QuadraticPrimeImplicantStrategy, WatcherBasedPrimeImplicantStrategy
public interface PrimeImplicantStrategy

The aim of those classes is to reduce the model found by a SAT solver into a prime implicant. See Computing prime implicants, David Deharbe, Pascal Fontaine, Daniel Le Berre and Bertrand Mazure @ FMCAD 2013 for details.

作成者:
leberre

メソッドの概要
 int[] compute(Solver<? extends DataStructureFactory> solver)
          returns a prime implicant from a solver object known to contain a model.
 int[] getPrimeImplicantAsArrayWithHoles()
          returns the prime implicant as an array with hole.
 

メソッドの詳細

compute

int[] compute(Solver<? extends DataStructureFactory> solver)
returns a prime implicant from a solver object known to contain a model.

パラメータ:
solver -
戻り値:
an sequence of Dimacs literals corresponding to the implicant.

getPrimeImplicantAsArrayWithHoles

int[] getPrimeImplicantAsArrayWithHoles()
returns the prime implicant as an array with hole. This is convenient to check if a particular variable belong to the prime implicant computed by compute(Solver). Must be called after compute(Solver).
